task.summary: Commit 1. First commit is for proposal on on Project 5. Includes description of project as well as timeline on when I will be completing specific events.
Commit 3, had to change the formatting the file
Commit 4, I added something to the proposal.
Commit 5. Added the main server and class for log entry object
Commit 6. Added classes and servlets for logEntryList and sending out appendRpc's for checking if secondaries are alive and if primary is alive. Working on finishing the implementation for them
Commit 7. Working on adding more functionality to heartbeat messages and working on election algorithm.
Commit 8. Working on the election algorithm
Commit 9. Working on the election algorithm and RequestVote RPC functionality.
Commit 10. Finished RequestVoteServlet and most of the election algorithm, will have to alter a bit once I finish replication part of the project.
Commit 11. Modified the appendEntryRpc servlet and the voteEntryRpc servlets.
Commit 11. Modified the appendEntryRpc servlet and the voteEntryRpc servlets.
Commit 12. Created a ReplicationRequests class to send appendEntryRpc's to the leader in order to store data in the form of json objects.
Commit 13. Refactored code in the Servermain class, AppendEntryServlet, RequestVoteServlet, and SecondaryFunctions class.
Commit 14. Refactored code in AppendEntryServlet and completed basic replication

Commit 15. Added and tested committing to a persistent data store. For each commit I am writing the JsonArray logEntry onto the json file that corresponds to the service. There is one json file for each service that will store persistent data and they are identified by the port number of the service.
Commit 16. Uploaded everything on the cloud and tested everything.
Commit 17. I refactored the code by making some functions smaller, deleting old code, and unnecessary comments.
